nts of all ages under the direction of Radiologists. Emergency Department The Emergency Department offers 24-hour Emergency Care with state-of-the-art equipment. The Forward Progression Concept allows you to see a physician sooner, keeps you moving through treatment spaces and assures that you are always within sight of nursing staff. Food & Nutrition Services The Food and Nutrition Services Department serves you balanced, nutritious, and appetizing meals according to the diet prescribed by your physician. Meals are prepared and served in a safe and sanitary environment. A selective menu is offered each day with the next day\x92s meal choices. Infusion Therapy Center The Infusion Therapy Center is located on the 3rd Floor in the Cancer Center of Acadiana at Abbeville General wing. It provides intravenous infusion treatment and injections to patients on an outpatient basis. Intensive Care Unit The Intensive Care Unit of Abbeville General Hospital is a multipurpose unit designed and equipped for the intensive treatment of critically ill patients with a variety of diagnoses. The Intensive Care Unit is a 6-bed unit located on the 2nd Floor with one bed designated for Inpatient Dialysis. Interventional Pain Therapy AGH Interventional Pain Therapy provides therapeutic outpatient services for individuals experiencing pain in the lower back and lower extremities. Labor & Delivery, Newborn Nursery Experience the comforts of home with the safety and security of a hospital setting. Our team of caring professionals\xa0will treat you like family, while providing high quality services during your labor, delivery, and postpartum recovery -- even if your pregnancy is considered "high risk." Laboratory/Pathology The Laboratory Department at Abbeville General Hospital is a full service laboratory --\xa0operating 24 hours per day,\xa07 days per week. We\xa0provide comprehensive services including diagnostic testing in the areas of chemistry, therapeutic drugs, coagulation, serology, blood banking, microbiology, hematology, urinalysis and immunology. Medical/Surgical Inpatient Care Abbeville General Hospital provides inpatient services for a full range of medical and surgical conditions and across all ages. Outpatient Surgery We have created a section of this website to guide you and provide you with peace of mind about your upcoming surgery. Please read this carefully as the instructions will help you move smoothly through each phase of your surgery and recovery. Partial Program The Partial Hospitalization Program provides an intensive psychiatric treatment resource to improve a patient's level of functioning and reduce symptoms to prevent relapse or hospitalization. Rural Health Clinics AGH Clinic , Women's Health of Vermilion , Pediatric Clinic , Erath/Delcambre Community Clinic and Maurice Community Care Clinic have been developed by Abbeville General Hospital to serve our community's healthcare needs. Each clinic offers a wide range of services, including Coumadin Management and reproductive health care and screening services. Sleep Center at Abbeville General Located on the third floor of our hospital, Sleep Center at Abbeville General provides overnight sleep studies for evaluation and diagnosis of obstructive sleep apnea (OSA) and other sleep disorders. Social Services The Social Services/Discharge Planning Department insures that each patient admitted to the hospital has a planned program for needed continuity of care and/or follow-up at discharge. Specialty Physician Clinic Abbeville General Hospital offers lease office space in the Specialty Clinic for area Physician Specialists to accommodate our local population. Physician specialists operate a satellite office by way of this lease arrangement. Surgical Services With three Operating Suites, two Minor Procedure Suites, an Endoscopy Suite, a Post-Anesthesia Care Unit (PACU), a Day Surgery/Outpatient unit, and a Holding area, we offer a wide variety of services, including minor procedures, parenteral therapy, inpatient surgeries and outpatient surgeries. Telemedicine Telemedicine Services now offered at Abbeville General Hospital Clinic are Hematology/Oncology, Endocrinology, Cardiology, Infectious Disease, Hepatitis Clinic, Pulmonology, Gastroenterology, Nephrology, Rheumatology and General Internal Medicine. Volunteer Services The Volunteers at Abbeville General Hospital are truly a special group of dedicated, compassionate and caring individuals who volunteer their time to assist our patients, visitors and staff. They help the hospital achieve its mission to provide high quality, cost effective health care services and to promote these services in the community. Home | Career Opportunities | Employee Login | Site Map | Search Site | About AGH | Find a Provider | Services | Patient & Guest Resources | News & Events | Locations & Contacts \xa9 Copyright 2017, Abbeville General Hospital.  All rights reserved. #disclaim{	text-align:center;} This Institution is an Equal Opportunity Provider and Employer.']

