e call Gloria Pierce at (337) 898-6494. Who Can Volunteer? Anyone can volunteer. Abbeville General Hospital Volunteers are professionals, students, homemakers and retirees who want to make a contribution in someone's life, as well as their community. Meeting new friends, learning new skills, and exploring new interests are a few of the rewards of volunteering. Volunteers help Abbeville General's staff deliver the highest quality patient care possible-volunteers do make a difference. Tree of Life/ Scholarship Program The Volunteers unveiled the Tree of Life, which is located in the main lobby of the hospital, on February 29, 1996 . The leaves on the tree represent donations in memory of a deceased loved one or to honor the living. Donations from the Tree of Life are dedicated to a Scholarship Program for college students enrolled in a health care related curriculum. Who May Apply Any college student who has attained at least Junior Year status and has: Lived in Vermilion Parish for a period of two (2) consecutive years, Enrolled in a health care related field at an accredited College or University in the State of Louisiana. Completed enough hours to be a Junior or Senior, and Maintained a 3.0 GPA or higher. You may download the application or call 337-898-6472 to obtain additional information regarding the Scholarship Program sponsored by the Abbeville General Hospital Volunteer Organization. Home | Career Opportunities | Employee Login | Site Map | Search Site | About AGH | Find a Provider | Services | Patient & Guest Resources | News & Events | Locations & Contacts \xa9 Copyright 2017, Abbeville General Hospital.  All rights reserved. #disclaim{	text-align:center;} This Institution is an Equal Opportunity Provider and Employer.']

